✅ All Fixes Applied
CIVIL SIDE
1. Video Playback (report/list.tsx + backend/server.py)

Backend now serves video files with HTTP Range Request support (StreamingResponse with 206 Partial Content) — this is required for video players to stream and seek properly on mobile
Frontend video player now passes Range and Accept headers, and uses onPlaybackStatusUpdate for better load detection
2. Panic Button — App Closing (civil/panic-active.tsx)

Uses Location.Accuracy.BestForNavigation for the most precise GPS coordinates at the moment of panic activation
On Android: calls BackHandler.exitApp() to fully close the app
On iOS: redirects to login screen (iOS prevents programmatic app termination — minimize is the platform-correct behavior)
When reopened, checkActivePanic() correctly shows the "I'm Safe Now" screen
3. "I'm Safe Now" → Security Dashboard Disappears

The deactivate_panic API sets is_active: False; the security panics endpoint filters is_active: True — the 15s auto-refresh on the security side will remove the panic from the list
